  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8a\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0ba3\u0bbf \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b8e\u0bb8\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0bb8\u0bcd.\u0baa\u0bbf. \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb3 \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Attack on Journalists - Suspended Police Task Force S.S.P. Return to service",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Amidst the protests that started demanding the resignation of the President and the Prime Minister, Sirasa, who went for media activities, Shakti TV. Senior Superintendent of Police Romesh Lienake, who was suspended in connection with the incident in which four journalists were attacked in front of the house of President Ranil Wickremesinghe (who was the Prime Minister at the time of the incident), has been called back to duty. Information from the police headquarters revealed this.",
        "When Ranil Wickremesinghe was the Prime Minister on the 9th, 6 journalists were attacked in front of his house during media activities. Following this, on the orders of the Inspector General of Police, Senior Superintendent of Police Romesh Lienake, who was the commanding officer of the police team that attacked the journalists, was suspended.",
        "However, as Ranil Wickramasinghe was sworn in as the 8th Executive President yesterday, it is learned that a letter has been sent by the Inspector General of Police inviting Senior Police Inspector Romesh Lienake to return to service.",
        "The Colombo Crime Prevention Unit has started investigations into the incident where journalists were attacked. In this regard, the officers of the Colombo Crime Prevention Unit presented the matters through a report to the Colombo Additional Magistrate Harshana Kekunawala on the 12th and received orders for investigations.",
        "Accordingly, Justice Harshana Kekunawala ordered all the media to provide the unedited videos related to the attack to the investigators.",
        "On the night of the 9th, Sirasa TV's video cameraman Varuna Sampath, office reporter Sarasi Peiris, internet journalist Jannitha Mendis Sakthi R.V. went to collect information about the tension near the then Prime Minister's residence. It is noteworthy that 6 people including journalist Sindhujan were attacked by the police on duty there."
      ],
